<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 8:35PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm in east central Sanilac County through 930
PM EDT...
At 833 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Carsonville, or near Deckerville, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds around 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds and hail are capable of minor damage to outdoor
objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Carsonville around 845 PM EDT.
Applegate around 900 PM EDT.
Port Sanilac around 910 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Forester and McGregor.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
